## Z-State: :flow

The system exists in continuous motion—never crystallizing into fixed 
hierarchies yet maintaining coherent structure through dynamic equilibrium. 
Power is always moving, trust always being negotiated, representation 
always provisional.

## Tendency Vector

Resonance/Structure tension (ρ↑μ↓ vs σ↑λ↑)

The gravitational pull toward superdelegate concentration battles the 
dispersive force of revocability and granularity. The system oscillates 
between:
- River state: distributed, flowing, granular
- Reservoir state: concentrated, pooled, superdelegate-heavy

The nemetic drift (ε) pushes toward whichever configuration better 
resonates with the network's affective topology at any given moment.

