## Nemetic Drift Prediction

Short-term (1-2 cycles): ρ↑ — superdelegate concentration as early 
adopters gain trust networks

Medium-term (3-5 cycles): σ↑λ↑ — granularity and revocability activate 
as concentration risks become visible

Long-term (6+ cycles): μ↑ — platform architecture codifies lessons 
into structural safeguards

Equilibrium: Dynamic oscillation around ρ≈μ with σ and λ as 
corrective forces
